  "title": "LLM Provider Environment Variables Ignored in Provider Selection",
  "vecs": [
    {
      "text": "## Problem\n\nThe Exaix daemon ignores `EXA_LLM_PROVIDER` and `EXA_LLM_MODEL` environment variables when selecting which AI provider to use for request processing. Despite these variables being correctly set in the daemon's environment, the provider selection logic always falls back to the mock provider due to preferring \"free\" providers.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n```bash\n# 1. Set environment variables for real LLM provider\nexport EXA_LLM_PROVIDER=google\nexport EXA_LLM_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash-exp\n\n# 2. Start daemon with these variables\nexactl daemon start\n\n# 3. Verify variables are set in daemon process\ncat /proc/$(pgrep -f \"exactl daemon\")/environ | tr '\\0' '\\n' | grep EXA_LLM\n# Shows: EXA_LLM_PROVIDER=google, EXA_LLM_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash-exp",
